                     <interp inst="t18430508-1445-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430508-cd-45" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430508-1445-offence-1 t18430508-cd-45"></join>13th of March</rs>, 1 copper, value 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18430508-name-306" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-306" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-306" type="surname" value="HOWSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-306" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430508-1445-offence-1 t18430508-name-306"></join>Mary Howse</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-307" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-307" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-307" type="surname" value="HOWSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-307" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY HOWSE</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner lived with a lodger of mine at my house—I saw my copper safe in the morning of the 10th of March, and missed it next day—it was fixed—I told the prisoner I had lost it—he told me to be quiet for two or three days, and he dare say I should hear of it—I have not found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-308" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-308" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-308" type="surname" value="BIRCH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-308" type="given" value="ANDREW"></interp>ANDREW BIRCH</persName>
                  </hi>. I lodge at this house. The prisoner lodged with me, and left on the 13th of March, to go to a place at Highbury-vale—he said he would return on Sunday, but did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-309" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-309" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-309" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS COX</persName>
                  </hi>. I know the prisoner. I saw him on the 10th of March, at Hoxton New-town, about 100 yards from the prosecutrix's, with the copper on his head in a sack—I said, "<hi rend="italic">Bill</hi>, where are you going with that?"—he said, "I am going to carry a washing-tub to King's-cross"—I said, "It is a copper"—he said, "No it ain't, it is a washing-tub"—I said it was not, and he went on—I am sure it was a copper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He could not see what it was through the sack. Witness. I saw it through the head of the sack.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-310" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-310" type="surname" value="DEANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-310" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT DEANS</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at Worship-street on the 15th, when the prisoner was locked in a cell—he called me to the window, asked me to go to Mrs. Howse, and ask her to be as lenient as possible, and as soon as he got out he, or his friends would buy her another copper.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184305080034"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">HUMPHERY</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Mayor.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I know nothing about it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
